headline: Robinhood Stock Tumbles as Crypto-Related Revenue Falls Short of Expectations
summary: Shares of  Robinhood  Markets were falling in after hours trading on Tuesday after the brokerage firm reported mixed fourth-quarter earnings due to lower cryptocurrency-related revenue.  Analysts had expected Robinhood to report revenue of $1.35 billion, according to FactSet.  Shares of Robinhood dropped 7.3% in after hours trading.

headline: Robinhood (NASDAQ:HOOD) Misses Q4 CY2025 Sales Expectations
summary: Financial services company Robinhood (NASDAQ:HOOD) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, but sales rose 26.5% year on year to $1.28 billion. Its GAAP profit of $0.66 per share was 3.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Robinhood stock drops on Q4 revenue miss, crypto slowdown
summary: Investing and brokerage platform Robinhood Markets (HOOD) released its fourth quarter results, which consisted of adjusted earnings of $0.66 per share and net revenue that just fell shy of Wall Street expectations ($1.28 billion vs. estimates of $1.35 billion). The stock is dropping in Tuesday's after-hours trading in response to these results. Market Domination Overtime Host Josh Lipton dives into the earnings release, taking a closer look at Robinhood's crypto revenue.
